    • getViewGroup

      public TaggedMap getViewGroup()
      Get ViewGroup TaggedMap and null if not defined.

      This will represent name-value pairs that define the view and orientation of this object. Compound elements will have its names flattened or normalized with any namespace prepended to the name and each name appended with a slash (/) delimiter as in a XPATH like syntax.

      For KML context a ViewGroup will represent a Camera or LookAt with name-values pairs for properties such as latitude, longitude, tilt, etc. Also supported are non-simple name-value pairs such as Google Extensions (E.g., gx:AltitudeMode, and gx:TimeSpan). Only difference with gx:TimeStamp is the prefix is prepended to the name. gx:TimeSpan as in following KML example is a compound value with the begin child element encoded as gx:TimeSpan/begin and likewise for the end element. 

           <LookAt>
        <gx:TimeSpan>
            <begin>2010-05-28T02:02:09Z</begin>
            <end>2010-05-28T02:02:56Z</end>
        </gx:TimeSpan>
        <longitude>143.1066665234362</longitude>
        <latitude>37.1565775502346</latitude>
     </LookAt>
      Returns:
      TaggedMap or null if none is defined

    • setRegion

      public void setRegion(Geodetic2DBounds bbox)
      Set Region on feature. Caller should set minLodPixels on the region TaggedMap instance after calling this method since this is not defined here and it is a required field.
      Parameters:
      bbox - Bounding box from which to set the region. If bbox Geodetic3DBounds instance then minAltitude and maxAltitude will be ignored by default. To preserve the min/max altitude of the bbox call setRegion(Geodetic2DBounds, boolean) with true value instead.

    • setRegion

      public void setRegion(Geodetic2DBounds bbox, boolean allowAltitude)
      Set Region on feature.

      Caller should set minLodPixels on the region TaggedMap instance after calling this method since this is not defined here and it is a required field. As defined in KML 2.2 OGC 07-147r2: if minAltitude and maxAltitude are both present, altitudeMode shall not have a value of clampToGround so in this case absolute is assumed if the altitudeMode property is not already set. Caller should therefore explicitly set altitudeMode if altitude will be included in the region.

      Parameters:
      bbox - Bounding box from which to set the region.
      allowAltitude - If set to true and bbox is a Geodetic3DBounds instance then minAltitude and maxAltitude properties will be set accordingly otherwise region will not include altitude.
